{"id":1114,"date":"2020-11-02T20:26:57","date_gmt":"2020-11-02T19:26:57","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/thimun-online.org\/?page_id=1114"},"modified":"2022-12-28T13:47:13","modified_gmt":"2022-12-28T12:47:13","slug":"mun-terminology-during-debate","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/thimun-online.org\/preparing-for-thimun\/mun-terminology-during-debate\/","title":{"rendered":"THIMUN TERMINOLOGY"},"content":{"rendered":"<section class=\"wpb-content-wrapper\"><p>[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h1>THIMUN TERMINOLOGY DURING DEBATE<\/h1>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221;][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/6&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-2&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;18412&#8243; img_size=&#8221;full&#8221; alignment=&#8221;right&#8221;][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;5\/6&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-10&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h2>Definition Of Key Words Used In The Forums<\/h2>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/5&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-2&#8243;][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;2\/5&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-10&#8243;][vc_column_text]<strong>The chair: <\/strong>The chairman or chairperson is the one conducting the debate and maintaining order while remaining totally impartial.<\/p>\n<p><strong>The House: <\/strong>All the members of the forum except the chairman.<\/p>\n<p><strong>The submitter: <\/strong>The person who is proposing the motion in the form of a draft resolution for debate.<\/p>\n<p><strong>The motion: <\/strong>The proposal for debate, which will eventually be voted upon.<\/p>\n<p><strong>A point of information: <\/strong>\u00a0A question directed either to the speaker who has the floor or to the chairman by a delegate of the House who has been duly recognised by the chairman.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;2\/5&#8243;][vc_column_text]<strong>A point of order:\u00a0<\/strong>A question directed to the chairman by a delegate of the House who feels that a mistake has been made in the order of debate or who requires clarification of the rules of procedure.<\/p>\n<p><strong>A point of personal privilege<\/strong>: A question directed to the chairman by a delegate who refers to the comfort and well-being of the house (e.g.: audibility, temperature in the house).<\/p>\n<p><strong>To have the floor: <\/strong>To have been given the right to speak in debate before the House.<\/p>\n<p><strong>To yield the floor: <\/strong>To give up one\u2019s right to the floor either finally or temporally for a point of information to be asked.[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/6&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-2&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;18413&#8243; img_size=&#8221;full&#8221; alignment=&#8221;right&#8221;][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;5\/6&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-10&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h2>Modes Of Address During Formal Debates<\/h2>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/5&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-2&#8243;][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;2\/5&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-10&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h3>A) Parliamentary behaviour by delegates<\/h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Speakers need to address each other in the <strong>Third Person\u00a0<\/strong>at all times. Always \u201c<em>honourable speaker<\/em>\u201d or \u201c<em>fellow deleg<\/em>ates\u201d, never \u201c<em>You<\/em>\u201d or \u201c<em>I<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>Delegates must avoid the use of insulting or abusive language.<\/li>\n<li>Delegates should address the chair and the House before presenting their speech<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>Example: \u201c <em>Honourable Chair, fellow delegates\u2026<\/em>\u201d[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;2\/5&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;18414&#8243; img_size=&#8221;full&#8221;][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/5&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-2&#8243;][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;4\/5&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-10&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h3>B) Phrases to be used by delegates of the House<\/h3>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/5&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-2&#8243;][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;2\/5&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-10&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>\u201c<em>Mr.\/Madam Chairman<\/em>\u2026\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The<\/em><em>delegate of \u2026 requests the floor<\/em>\u201d or \u201c<em>wishes the floor<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The<\/em><em>delegate of \u2026<\/em><em>would like to rise a point of information\/ point of order<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The<\/em><em>delegate of \u2026 wishes to speak in favour of\/against this motion\/resolution\/amendment because\u2026<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>Is the chair \/the speaker (not) aware that\u2026<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;2\/5&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>\u00a0\u201c<em>Does the speaker (not) agree with me that\u2026<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u00a0\u201c<em>The speaker stated in his\/her speech\u2026 Doe he\/she (not) realize that\u2026<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u00a0\u201c<em>The delegate of \u2026 moves to amend the resolution by striking\/inserting\/adding the words\u2026<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u00a0\u201c<em>The delegate of \u2026 urges the House to give its support by voting for\/against this motion\/resolution\/ amendment<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/5&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-2&#8243;][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;4\/5&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h3>C) Phrases to be used by the chairman<\/h3>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/5&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-2&#8243;][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;2\/5&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-10&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>\u201c<em>The House will come to order<\/em>\u201d or \u201c<em>Will the house please come to order<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The chair calls upon the delegate of \u2026 (the submitter) to read the resolution to the House<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The House has heard the resolution. Is there a second?<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The chair fixes a debate time of 10 minutes for and 10 minutes against the motion<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The delegate of \u2026 has the floor<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>All points are out of order until the speaker has concluded his\/her speech<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The chair recognizes the delegate of\u2026<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>To what point does the delegate of \u2026 rise?<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>Please rise and state you point of information\/point of order<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>Will you please state your point in a form of a question<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The speaker appears not to have heard\/understood your question<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>Will you please repeat\/rephrase your question<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>Are there any further points on the floor?<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>Are there any further points of information to this speaker?<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>There is a point of order on the floor. Please rise and state your point<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>Your point is (not) well taken<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;2\/5&#8243;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>\u201c<em>Will the speaker please make his\/her concluding remarks<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>Debate time for\/against the resolution\/the amendment has been exhausted\/has expired. Will the speaker please yield the floor<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The chair proposes an extension of debate time by 5 minutes for and 5 minutes against the motion<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The debate is now closed. We will moved into voting procedures<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>All points are out of order<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The motion will now be put to the vote<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>Will all those in favour of the resolution\/the amendment, please raise their placards<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>Will all those opposed to against\/against the resolution, please raise their placards<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>Will all those abstaining, please raise their placards<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The motion\/the rzesolution\/the amendment has passed by\u2026<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>The motion\/the resolution\/the amendment has failed by\u2026<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>With x votes in favour, y votes against and z votes abstaining, the motion\/the resolution\/the amendment has passed\/failed<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<li>\u201c<em>Clapping is (not) in order<\/em>\u201d.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]<\/p>\n<\/section>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text] THIMUN TERMINOLOGY DURING DEBATE [\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221;][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/6&#8243; offset=&#8221;vc_col-xs-2&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;18412&#8243; img_size=&#8221;full&#8221; alignment=&#8221;right&#8221;][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;5\/6&#8243; offset=&#8221;